26 PART II. PROSTATE CANCER CONTROL PROGRAM
27 SECTION 2.1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
28 Health and Human Services, Division of Public Health, the sum of two million dollars
29 ($2,000,000) in recurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be used to establish and
30 administer a statewide Prostate Cancer Control Program that provides free or low-cost prostate
31 cancer screenings and follow-up to any man residing in North Carolina who meets all of the
32 following criteria:
33 (1) Is uninsured or underinsured.
34 (2) Is not a beneficiary of Medicare Part B or Medicaid.
35 (3) Is between 50 and 70 years of age and without a family history of prostate
36 cancer or is between 40 and 70 years of age with a family history of prostate
37 cancer. For the purpose of this subdivision, a man with a family history of
38 prostate cancer means any man with at least one first-degree relative who (i)
39 was diagnosed with prostate cancer, (ii) developed prostate cancer, (iii) died
40 as a result of prostate cancer, (iv) was diagnosed with a cancer known to be
41 associated with increased risk of prostate cancer, or (v) has a genetic alteration
42 known to be associated with increased risk of prostate cancer.
43 (4) Has a household income below two hundred fifty percent (250%) of the
44 federal poverty level.
45
46 PART III. HEALTH INSURANCE REGULATION CHANGES TO CREATE PARITY
47 FOR SUPPLEMENTAL AND DIAGNOSTIC BREAST IMAGING
48 SECTION 3.1.(a) G.S. 58-51-57 is recodified as G.S. 58-3-271.
49 SECTION 3.1.(b) G.S. 58-65-92 is repealed.
50 SECTION 3.1.(c) G.S. 58-67-76 is repealed.
