1 Reimbursements for laboratory fees shall be made only if the laboratory meets accreditation
2 standards adopted by the North Carolina Medical Care Commission.
3 (f) If the application of any provision of this section would render the insured ineligible
4 for a health savings account under section 223, then that provision shall apply only for
5 high-deductible health plans with respect to the deductible of that plan after the insured has
6 satisfied the minimum deductible under section 223, except with respect to items or services that
7 are preventive care. For items or services that are preventive care under section 223, all
8 provisions of this section shall apply regardless of whether or not the minimum deductible under
9 section 223 has been satisfied."
