26 PART IV. HEALTHCARE PROVIDER BILLING REGULATION CHANGES TO
27 CREATE PARITY FOR SUPPLEMENTAL AND DIAGNOSTIC BREAST CANCER
28 IMAGING
29 SECTION 4.1.(a) G.S. 90-701 is recodified as G.S. 90-705.
30 SECTION 4.1.(b) Article 41 of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes, as amended by
31 subsection (a) of this section, reads as rewritten:
32 "Article 41.
33 "Pathology Services Billing.Transparency in Healthcare Provider Billing Practices.
34 "§ 90-702. Definitions.
35 The following definitions shall apply in this Article:
36 (1) Breast cancer prevention service. – All services listed under
37 G.S. 58-3-271(b2).
38 (2) Cost-sharing. – As defined in G.S. 58-3-271.
39 (3) Reserved for future codification purposes.
40 (4) Health benefit plan. – As defined in G.S. 58-3-167.
41 (5) Health services facility. – A facility that is licensed under (i) Chapter 131E or
42 Chapter 122C of the General Statutes or (ii) the licensing laws of another state
43 for the provision of the same services in the ordinary course of business or
44 practice as would require the facility to be licensed under Chapter 131E or
45 Chapter 122C of the General Statutes were the facility located in this State.
46 (6) Healthcare provider. – A health services facility or a person who is licensed,
47 registered, or certified under Chapter 90 or Chapter 90B of the General
48 Statutes, or under the laws of another state, to provide healthcare services in
49 the ordinary care of business or practice, or as a profession, or in an approved
50 education or training program.
51 (7) Reserved for future codification purposes.
