1 (8) Insurer. – As defined in G.S. 58-3-167.
2 "§ 90-704. Billing for certain breast cancer prevention services.
3 (a) A healthcare provider who has not contracted with an insurer to participate in the
4 provider network of a health benefit plan shall accept as reimbursement for any breast cancer
5 prevention service provided to an individual insured under a health benefit plan the amount of
6 reimbursement provided by that insurer, including any cost-sharing required to be paid by the
7 patient.
8 (b) No healthcare provider may bill a patient covered under a health benefit plan or
9 request additional reimbursement from the insurer for any amount above the amount required to
10 be accepted under subsection (a) of this section.
11 …."
